Bucatini Cacio e Pepe

1 lb dired bucatini pasta
1 tbsp freshly ground black pepper + more for garnish
5 tbsp unsalted butter, divided
4 tbsp olive oil
1 c fresh grated parmesan cheese
1 c freshly grated pecorino romano cheese + more for garnish
kosher salt to taste

Bring a large pot of salted water to boil over high heat. Add the bucatini and cook until jsut al dente, 8-9 min. Drain, reserving 1 1/4 c of pasta water. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, toast the ground pepper over medium heat until fragrant, 30 sec. Add 4 tbsp of butter and the olive oil and cook, until the butter has melted, 1-2 min. Add the drained pasta, 1 c of the reserved water, the grated cheeses. Toss to coat the pasta well and season with salt. Add the remaining pasta water and tbsp of butter, tossing to incorporate. Transfer to a platter and garnish with ground pepper and cheese. Serve.

